</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,150,681]" pageId="12" pageNumber="523">
<specimenCount box="[199,213,583,609]" pageId="12" pageNumber="523" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
—Basal plate: species belonging to basal plate group 1 (
<figureCitation box="[865,950,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 38" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1850,1874]" captionTargetBox="[232,1354,953,1817]" captionTargetId="figure-59@24.[231,1356,944,1826]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 38. Female basal plate of ovipositor, with three configurations found in the known Brazilian species of Lestes: 1 (Lestes dichrostigma, Lestes pictus, Lestes tricolor and Lestes undulatus), 2 (Lestes forficula and Lestes paulistus) and 3 (Lestes minutus and Lestes demarcoi sp. nov.). Parts are named as follows: D—dorsal side, A—anterior side, V—ventral side, P—posterior side, PD—dorsal section of posterior side, PV—ventral section of posterior side, AP—Acute process (as defined in Westfall &amp; May (1996)), VA—anterior section of ventral side and VP—posterior section of ventral side." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5027090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5027090/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="523">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
), with dorsal side longer than ventral side. Posterior side with ventral section twice the length of the dorsal section. Convex dorsal and ventral sides. Dorsal section of posterior side slightly concave (
<figureCitation box="[625,725,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 39" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[367,1222,183,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-17@25.[366,1222,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 39. Basal plate of ovipositor (The basal plate was kept in color while the rest was converted to grayscale to facilitate the visualization of the differences between species): A—Lestes dichrostigma, B—Lestes forficula, C—Lestes minutus, D— Lestes paulistus, E—Lestes pictus, F—Lestes tricolor, G—Lestes undulatus, H—Lestes demarcoi sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5027092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5027092/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="523">Fig. 39F</figureCitation>
). Pectoral color pattern as in 
<figureCitation box="[1051,1151,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[233,1355,192,1847]" captionTargetId="figure-19@26.[232,1356,181,1865]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 40. Pectoral color pattern: A—Lestes auritus (female), B—Lestes bipupillatus (female), C—Lestes dichrostigma (female), D—Lestes falcifer (male), E—Lestes fernandoi (male), F—Lestes forficula (female), G—Lestes jurzitzai (male), H— Lestes minutus (female), I—Lestes paulistus (female), J—Lestes pictus (female), K—Lestes quadristriatus (male), L—Lestes tricolor (female), M—Lestes undulatus (female), N—Lestes demarcoi sp. nov. (female)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5027096" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5027096/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="523">
Fig. 
<specimenCount box="[1102,1151,655,681]" pageId="12" pageNumber="523" type="generic">40L</specimenCount>
</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
